parameters: Perhaps I should first investigate the area before going back..
What an unusual looking object. What do you think it is, Dreamborn? Anything in your database?
According to the database, something familiar to this resemble a way to show the path to multiple locations.
Incredible! A wooden version of our interdimensional map. The writings on this one faded with time.
The example is not quite precise Captain.
The equivalent would be having a moltitude of these wooden directional pointers ..
Tin can, it's ok. I get it.
Another wooden pointer. Also in this one the writings are completely gone. I wonder what place was this.
A lightpost of sort. What do you make of it?
Perhaps Captain we are on an area
that was once populated with life.
An ancient lightpost. I wonder what was its color.
Oh\| my\| goodness.\| Is that a human?
Based from the size of the bones, it looks like more like local fauna, Sir.
Can you imagine this planet is actually crawlig with human-eating beasts?
That Sir, it is still not excluded.
Dreamborn, sometimes you should just stop talking.
A lightpost of sort. What do you make of it?
Perhaps Captain we are on an area
that was once populated with life.
An ancient lightpost. I wonder what was its color.
The earthquake caused by the phaser, opened a sealed door carved into the side of the mountain.
Whether this is by fate or by accident, I can't deny the curiosity to enter this place.
Dreamborn, let's stay alert and set your phaser to stun.
Look at this. An ancient building. Analysis Dreamborn. Is it safe to proceed?
There is a 50% chance that moving the rubble can cause a general collapse of the building.
This is really well stucked. I will use my phaser.
Uh oh. Sir, my scan indicates a series of shockwaves moving underneath the building.
Sir, my scan detects a cave 3 clicks back towards the plain.
I can detect a chamber at the end of the cave from here. Not sure if man-made or completely natural.
Great! The entrance of the building completely collapsed.
Nothing to see here. The whole interior collapsed.
Sir, with the junk material in this box, I can create a better version of your current Phaser.
